cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about saliency detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a new network architecture that focuses on effective high-level context features and low-level spatial structural features, which involves machine learning techniques such as attention mechanisms and loss functions. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper uses a loss function to guide the network to learn more detailed information in boundary localization, which involves optimization techniques and could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
